title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1971-12-31
lineage: Master Reel (Technics 1506) > Behringer Ultralink Pro MX882 > KORG MR-2000S (DSF 1-bit/5.6MHz) > KORG AudioGate (WAV 24-bit/96k)  Mastering Info: WAV (24-bit/96k) > Samplitude Pro X6 Suite (16-bit/48k) > FLAC/16
description:
Set I
Bill Graham Intro
Dancing In The Streets
Mr. Charlie
Brown Eyed Women
Beat It On Down The Line
You Win Again
Jack Straw
Sugaree
El Paso
Chinatown Shuffle
Tennessee Jed
Mexicali Blues
China Cat Sunflower >
I Know You Rider
Next Time You See Me
Playing In The Band
Loser
One More Saturday Night *
Set II
Bill Graham Intro
Stars & Stripes Forever
Truckin' >
Drums >
The Other One >
Me & My Uncle >
The Other One
Black Peter
Big River
The Same Thing
Ramble On Rose
Sugar Magnolia
Not Fade Away >
Goin' Down The Road Feeling Bad >
Not Fade Away

Encore:
Casey Jones

Comment
FM broadcast KSAN-San Francisco
Yogi Phlegm performed
New Riders Of The Purple Sage performed

During Set I Weir explained that the organ and piano weren't in tune with each other and they were going to have to decide which to tune to. Hence the constant tuning breaks.

Jerry Garcia - Guitar
Bob Weir - Guitar
Ron "Pigpen" Mckernan - Hammond B3, Harmonica
Keith Godchaux - Piano
Phil Lesh - Bass
Bill Kretuzmann - Drums
Donna Jean Godchaux - Vocals * (first time performing with the band)
